[ext_resource type="Script" uid="uid://b6tmiam3vo7cr" path="res://Resources/PatchNote.gd" id="1_62m15"]

[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_62m15")
patch_version = &"v0.4.0"
patch_notes = "New Features:
- Consumption numbers have been tweaked on both the Orbital Launcher V1 and V2 for accuracy.
- A new Undo and Redo feature has been added
   - The program will keep track of the last 15 actions taken in the program and will allow you to scrub backwards and forwards on all 15 of those as you need.
- Eyedropper tool has been added with two modes:
   - Standard mode will begin the build mode for the building your mouse is hovering over. removing the need to go into the build menu in some situations.
   - Alternate mode will begin the build mode for the building your mouse is hovering over and also copy the recipe assigned to that building.
- Mass selection tool is now in place. Users can now click and drag to select multiple buildings in the environment
	- pressing alt with the buildings selected and your mouse over any one of them will allow you to relocate all of the selected buildings and maintain their spacing
	- pressing alt and tapping R on any building will now allow you to rotate an already placed building as needed.
- "What If" Scenario analyzer has been added.
	- users can identify the target recipe they want to build up to, the desired production per minute of the target recipe and identify any V2 buildings they'd like to use to get there. The planner will tell you the entire chain of recipes or buildings that will be needed to make that recipe and rate happen
	- Users can print a PDF copy of the analysis report for easy review.
	- Users can also ask the build planner to make a rough draft of the buildings needed to accomplish the desired what-if scenario.
	- **BE AWARE, THE ROUGH DRAFT GENERATION IS INTENDED TO GET YOU 80% OF THE WAY TO A FUNCTIONAL BUILD PLAN. IT WILL NOT CREATE A PERFECTED BUILD PLAN FIRST TRY**
- New rail visibility options added in. Pressing the V button by default will now allow you to change how the rails are visible:
	- Standard - Rails will sit behind buildings as they did in previous versions
	- High visibility - Rails will sit on top of buildings so shorter runs can be easier to read.
	- None - Rails will be invisible for the time being but still remain mapped.
	- High visibility mode also comes with an Alpha slider so you can adjust the transparency of the rails should you want to.
- Defense turret and Defense Tower are now added to the build planner marking the completion point of ALL buildings being fully integrated.
- Rails will now have badges on them that show overall throughput possible on the rails so it's easier to read what capacities are at a glance.

Bug Fixes
- When placing buildings now, the nodes for rails on the buildings will no longer be interactable meaning you don't need to be mindful where you click on a building to place it.
- The delete building button has been remapped by default to the "Delete" key to prevent accidental deletion. If you would like to remap it to the right mouse button or anything else, you are welcome to change it in the controls menu.
- the production pane will now properly scale with resolution along with the size being generally increased a little bit for better visibility.

"
known_issues = "-The planner generation from the what if engine leaves things REALLY widely spaced out and does not take advantage of rail support structures.

"
metadata/_custom_type_script = "uid://b6tmiam3vo7cr"
